page.title: 02ECOLOGY
page.content: This low lying area of Holderness has some land below sea level.The coast at Tunstall is subject to erosion.The land is used for farming and such crops as barley,wheat, and rape seed are grown.Some farmers have cows,pigs, sheep,hens,cattle and horses.Around Roos there are mixed deciduos woods. Fields are separated by hedges and dikes.There are quite a lot of wild animals like moles,rabbits,badgers, stoats and weasels plus a variety of wild birds,like pheasants,partridges and pigeons. The roads are very twisty and follow the shape of the fields and dikes.The nearest shopping centre is Withernsea but many people go to Hull for their main items of clothing and furniture. Withernsea is 5 miles away and Hull is 15miles away.
